.TH "nilfs_search_super_root" 9 "nilfs_search_super_root" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_search_super_root \- search the latest valid super root
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_search_super_root
.BI "(struct the_nilfs *nilfs "  ","
.BI "struct nilfs_recovery_info *ri "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nilfs" 12
the_nilfs
.IP "ri" 12
pointer to a nilfs_recovery_info struct to store search results.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_search_super_root\fP looks for the latest super-root from a partial
segment pointed by the superblock.  It sets up struct the_nilfs through
this search. It fills nilfs_recovery_info (ri) required for recovery.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned.  On error, one of the following
negative error code is returned.

-EINVAL - No valid segment found

-EIO - I/O error

-ENOMEM - Insufficient memory available.
